Coding for beginners
Scratch uses drag and drop
code blocks. This visual
approach makes it engaging and
enjoyable to create projects.
Level 1 (Learn to code animations)
We teach creating stories in Scratch which combines the art of
storytelling with the skills of programming. It nurtures creativity,
logical thinking and communication skills, while also providing a
platform for self-expression and digital literacy.
Duration: 8 Classes (1 hour each)
Age: 8 and above
Level 2 (Learn to write programs)
Learn about variables and data manipulation, conditional
statements and loops. Build programs like calculator, coin toss, etc.
Duration: 8 Classes (1 hour each)
Age: 8 and above
Level 3 (Learn to code games)
We teach game development which helps in using programming
concepts such as sequencing, conditionals, loops, variables and
event handling. It provides a practical context for understanding and
utilizing these concepts in a meaningful way. Students will learn to
build games like angry bird, ping-pong and much more.
Duration: 8 Classes (1 hour each)
Age: 9 and above
Level 4 (Learn Artiﬁcial Intelligence & Augmented Realty)
Learn to create a chatbot-like character, code games like Tic-Tac-Toe
player against computer, mask detectors and much more.
Duration: 8 Classes (1 hour each)
Age: 10 and above
App Development
Hands-on approach that allows
students to prototype and
deploy Android apps without
the need for complex coding.
Level 1
Learn about visual programming interface, component-based
development and live testing. You will be developing at least three
separate applications.
Duration: 8 Classes (1 hour each)
Age: 10 and above
Level 2
Learn to code complex multiple-page applications that includes
games, quizzes, etc. Learn to code sensors of mobile phones.
Duration: 8 Classes (1 hour each)
Age: 10 and above
Level 3
Learn to develop a full ﬂedged coee shop app. Combine UI with
data management. Develop customer and administration apps.
Create a messenger app and much more
Duration: 8 Classes (1 hour each)
Age: 11 and above
Robotics
Hands-on approach to design,
assemble and program the
robot. Build like an engineer.
Level 1
Learn to build a wired robot, line-follower robot, etc. Understand the
concepts of LED, resistor and IC. Learn to make an intruder-alert
circuit.
Duration: 8 Classes (1 hour each)
Age: 8 and above
Level 2
Learn to write a code to control your robot's behavior. This involves
programming the microcontroller to receive inputs from sensors,
make decisions and control the motors accordingly. Student will
learn to build doodle robots, Bluetooth robots and dierent circuits.
Duration: 8 Classes (1 hour each)
Age: 10 and above
Level 3
Learn advance robotics & learn to build voice-controlled robots,
maze-solver robots, joystick-controlled robots, etc.
Duration: 8 Classes (1 hour each)
Age: 11 and above
Level 4
Learn to build Otto Robot, matrix eyes and to make them work on
voice commands.
Duration: 8 Classes (1 hour each)
Age: 12 and above
CS50
A course by Harvard University
CS50 is an excellent introductory course in Computer Science. It
oers a comprehensive curriculum, engaging lectures and
challenging assignments, making it an attractive choice for
individuals seeking to develop their programming and Computer
Science knowledge and skills.
Upon successfully completing CS50, participants receive a
certiﬁcate of completion. The certiﬁcate can be used to
demonstrate proﬁciency in Computer Science fundamentals and
programming skills.
Languages covered: C, HTML, CSS, Python, SQL & Flask.
Duration: 150-160 sessions depending on student's capability.
Age: 13 and above
